      <h1>Commercial Kitchen Equipment: The Complete List India 2026</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span>📅 Updated: March 2026</span>
        <span>⏱️ 15 min read</span>
        <span>🇮🇳 India-focused</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Setting up a commercial kitchen in India in 2026? This is the complete list of commercial kitchen equipment you'll need</strong> — from cooking equipment and refrigeration to prep tables and dishwashing. Whether you're opening a restaurant, cloud kitchen, bakery, or café, this guide covers every category with real Indian prices and honest buying advice.</p>

    <h2>Commercial Kitchen Equipment: The Master List</h2>
    <p>Commercial kitchens need equipment in six key categories: cooking equipment, refrigeration, food preparation, storage, dishwashing, and ventilation. Let's go through each category in detail.</p>

    <h2>1. Cooking Equipment</h2>
    <p>The cooking equipment is the heart of your commercial kitchen. What you need depends entirely on your menu.</p>

    <h3>Commercial Cooking Ranges (Gas Stoves)</h3>
    <p>Gas ranges are the foundation of most Indian restaurant kitchens. Prices range from ₹8,000 for a basic 2-burner range to ₹90,000 for a heavy-duty 6-burner range with oven. When selecting a range, look for BTU output per burner (higher is better for fast cooking), heavy-duty cast iron grates, and ease of cleaning.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Price Range (INR)</th><th>Best For</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>2-Burner Range</td><td>₹8,000 – ₹25,000</td><td>Small cafés, cloud kitchens</td></tr>
        <tr><td>4-Burner Range</td><td>₹18,000 – ₹55,000</td><td>Medium restaurants</td></tr>
        <tr><td>6-Burner Range</td><td>₹35,000 – ₹90,000</td><td>Busy restaurants</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Chinese/Wok Range</td><td>₹25,000 – ₹80,000</td><td>Chinese/Thai cuisine</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tandoor</td><td>₹18,000 – ₹90,000</td><td>North Indian restaurants</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Commercial Ovens</h3>
    <p>Every commercial kitchen needs at least one oven. The type depends on your menu:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Convection oven</strong> (₹35,000 – ₹4,00,000): For bakeries, pastry shops, and restaurants with an in-house baking programme</li>
      <li><strong>Deck oven</strong> (₹65,000 – ₹9,00,000): For bread-focused bakeries needing bottom heat</li>
      <li><strong>Pizza oven</strong> (₹40,000 – ₹3,50,000): For pizzerias and restaurants with a pizza menu</li>
      <li><strong>Combi oven</strong> (₹3,00,000 – ₹15,00,000): The most versatile commercial oven — combines convection, steam, and combination cooking in one unit</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For a detailed breakdown, read our <a href="/blog/bakery-oven-price-india">Bakery Oven Price in India 2026</a> guide.</p>

    <h3>Deep Fryers</h3>
    <p>Essential for any restaurant serving fried items. Key considerations: oil capacity (bigger capacity = less frequent oil changes), recovery time (how quickly oil returns to temperature between batches), and filtration (some models have built-in filtration, extending oil life significantly). Prices range from ₹12,000 for a basic 6-litre model to ₹1,50,000 for a heavy-duty 30-litre commercial fryer.</p>

    <h3>Commercial Griddles & Tawas</h3>
    <p>A flat-top griddle or tawa is essential for Indian restaurants. Used for making rotis, dosas, parathas, and as a flat cooking surface for various dishes. Commercial griddles range from ₹12,000 to ₹80,000 depending on size and fuel type.</p>

    <h2>2. Refrigeration Equipment</h2>
    <p>Commercial refrigeration is critical for food safety compliance (FSSAI requirements) and ingredient quality. Never skimp on refrigeration.</p>

    <h3>Reach-In Refrigerators</h3>
    <p>The standard commercial refrigerator for kitchen use. Stainless steel construction, holds 2–8°C consistently, and available in 1-door (150–300L), 2-door (400–600L), and 3-door (700–900L) configurations. Prices: ₹25,000 – ₹2,00,000.</p>

    <h3>Under-Counter Refrigerators</h3>
    <p>Compact refrigerators that fit under prep tables. Keep ingredients close to the work area. Prices: ₹20,000 – ₹55,000.</p>

    <h3>Commercial Freezers</h3>
    <p>Chest freezers and upright freezers for storing frozen ingredients and par-cooked items. Commercial grade freezers maintain -18°C to -22°C consistently. Prices: ₹25,000 – ₹1,50,000.</p>

    <h3>Display Refrigerators</h3>
    <p>Glass-front display cases for showing bakery products, desserts, and cold beverages to customers. Prices: ₹35,000 – ₹2,50,000. Read our <a href="/refrigeration">Commercial Refrigeration guide</a> for detailed options.</p>

    <h2>3. Food Preparation Equipment</h2>
    <h3>Commercial Mixers</h3>
    <p>Essential for bakeries and restaurants with significant baking or mixing needs. Planetary mixers (₹18,000 – ₹4,00,000) handle cakes, pastries, and light doughs. Spiral mixers (₹35,000 – ₹5,00,000) are purpose-built for bread and pizza dough. Read our <a href="/mixers-and-processors">Mixers & Processors guide</a> for details.</p>

    <h3>Vegetable Cutting Machines</h3>
    <p>A commercial vegetable cutter saves hours of prep time in Indian restaurant kitchens. Prices: ₹25,000 – ₹90,000 for a good commercial model. Essential for high-volume kitchens.</p>

    <h3>Commercial Blenders</h3>
    <p>For smoothies, sauces, soups, and Indian chutneys and masalas. Commercial blenders are significantly more powerful than household models. Prices: ₹8,000 – ₹45,000.</p>

    <h3>Dough Sheeter / Roller</h3>
    <p>For bakeries making croissants, puff pastry, pizza bases, or pasta. Reduces manual labour significantly. Prices: ₹45,000 – ₹1,50,000.</p>

    <h2>4. Storage & Shelving</h2>
    <h3>Stainless Steel Work Tables</h3>
    <p>The workhorse of commercial kitchen prep areas. Heavy-gauge stainless steel with undershelves for storage. Standard sizes: 4ft, 6ft, and 8ft. Prices: ₹6,000 – ₹35,000 per table.</p>

    <h3>Commercial Shelving</h3>
    <p>NSF-approved chrome wire shelving or stainless steel shelving for dry storage, walk-in storage, and general organisation. Prices: ₹3,000 – ₹15,000 per unit.</p>

    <h3>Ingredient Bins & Containers</h3>
    <p>HDPE bins for bulk dry ingredients (flour, sugar, rice). Various sizes from 20L to 120L. Prices: ₹500 – ₹3,500 per bin.</p>

    <h2>5. Dishwashing & Sanitation</h2>
    <h3>Commercial Dishwashers</h3>
    <p>Manual dishwashing is slow and inconsistent. A commercial dishwasher pays for itself quickly in a busy restaurant by reducing labour costs and improving hygiene. Under-counter models: ₹65,000 – ₹1,50,000. Hood-type pass-through: ₹1,20,000 – ₹3,00,000.</p>

    <h3>Three-Compartment Sinks</h3>
    <p>Required by FSSAI regulations for proper dishwashing (wash, rinse, sanitise). Stainless steel construction. Prices: ₹8,000 – ₹35,000.</p>

    <h3>Handwashing Stations</h3>
    <p>Dedicated handwashing sinks are required in commercial kitchens. Prices: ₹3,500 – ₹15,000.</p>

    <h2>6. Ventilation & Exhaust</h2>
    <h3>Commercial Exhaust Hoods</h3>
    <p>A commercial exhaust hood is required by law in commercial kitchens. It removes heat, smoke, grease, and odours. Size is determined by the cooking line length. Wall-mounted hoods: ₹15,000 – ₹60,000 per metre of coverage. Read our <a href="/blog/commercial-exhaust-hood">Commercial Exhaust Hood guide</a> for details.</p>

